@startuml
autonumber
actor Customer
participant Device 
Activate Customer
participant DeviceProvisioningService #00FFFF
participant ProductIoTHub #00FFFF
participant FWProvider #FF00FF
note over Device, ProductIoTHub
    Device was registered for this product before
end note
== First start ==
Customer -> Device: Switch On/Power Up
... Booting up ...
Device -> DeviceProvisioningService: registerDevice(callback)
DeviceProvisioningService --> Device: callback.RegistrationResult(PROVISIONING_DEVICE_STATUS_ASSIGNED, IoTHubURI, deviceId)
ProductIoTHub -> Device: setProperties
Device -> ProductIoTHub: iamNewToYou(deviceId, firmwareversion)
opt Firmware needs to be updated
    ProductIoTHub -> Device: updateFWMandantory(URL)
    Device -> FWProvider: URL.get(OLDFW)
    FWProvider --> Device: FW, Checksum
    ... Downloading ...
    Device -> Device: CheckChecksum
    Device -> Device: update
    ... Installing ...
    Device -> Device: restart
    ... Booting up ...
    Device -> ProductIoTHub: iamNewToYou(deviceId, firmwareversion)
end opt
ProductIoTHub -> Device: youMayStartSending()

Device -> ProductIoTHub: sendData(Data)
... Working ...
== Claim/Remove ==
ProductIoTHub -> Device: youMustRetire()
Device -> Device: waits
opt if Device was not reached
    Device -> ProductIoTHub: sendData(Data)
    ProductIoTHub --> Device: Not registered
end opt
Device -> DeviceProvisioningService: registerDevice(callback)
DeviceProvisioningService --> Device: callback.RegistrationResult(PROVISIONING_DEVICE_STATUS_ERROR, null, null)
Device -> Device: NobodyLovesMeMode()
loop once a day
    Device -> DeviceProvisioningService: registerDevice(callback)
end loop
== IoT Hub not available ==
loop several times
    Device -> ProductIoTHub: sendData(Data)
    ProductIoTHub --> Device: NotAvailable/Network Error
end loop
Device -> DeviceProvisioningService: registerDevice(callback)
DeviceProvisioningService --> Device: callback.RegistrationResult(PROVISIONING_DEVICE_STATUS_ASSIGNED, IoTHubURI, deviceId)
Device -> Device: compare IoTHub and change if necessary
note over Device, ProductIoTHub
    if connection is now successfull, go on. If not and IoT Hub has not changed
    repeat with low frequence. Also if DPS is not available.
end note

@enduml
